Ad Text:
About Us

Fortescue is both a proud West Australian company and a global green solutions business. We are recognised for our culture, innovation and industry-leading development of infrastructure, mining assets and green energy initiatives.

Our Opportunity

Work Location: Perth Office - Fortescue's Perth office is located on the traditional lands of the Whadjuk Noongar people

Roster: Monday to Friday

Fortescue is transforming its business using AI and data to automate, optimise, and decarbonise operations across mining and energy. The Data and AI Platform team builds and maintains the technical foundations that enable scalable, secure, and high-impact AI delivery.

The AI Platform team is responsible for architecting and engineering reusable AI components, orchestration frameworks, and cloud-based infrastructure that support data scientists, engineers, and digital product teams across the business. Our work enables consistent, trusted, and efficient development of GenAI agents, MLOps workflows, and enterprise-grade AI applications.

Key Responsibilities

Design, build, and maintain scalable AI platform capabilities, including AI agents, copilots, and LLM-driven workflows, ensuring alignment with enterprise standards
Integrate AI solutions seamlessly into critical business workflows while ensuring compliance with architecture, security, and data governance frameworks
Prototype and evaluate emerging AI technologies to validate technical feasibility and deliver operational value through rapid experimentation
Collaborate effectively in agile, cross-functional teams to deliver AI solutions that meet business requirements and architectural best practices.
Qualifications and Experience

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Artificial Intelligence or a related field
Demonstrated in CV experience designing, developing, and delivering AI/ML systems, including cloud-native solutions
Strong proficiency in Python; familiarity with TypeScript/JavaScript, C#, or Go
Practical expertise with ML/AI frameworks like PyTorch, TensorFlow, Hugging Face, and LangChain
Exposure to Generative AI and Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) approaches, embedding models, vector stores, and agent orchestration
Working knowledge of cloud platforms (AWS or Azure), containerization (Docker), orchestration (Kubernetes), infrastructure-as-code (Terraform), and CI/CD pipelines
Familiarity with data and platform engineering tools such as Snowflake, Kafka, AWS S3, REST APIs, microservices, and knowledge graph integration
Experience contributing to Agile delivery teams, using Git and GitHub for version control and tools like Jira for project tracking.

Our Commitment

Fortescue is deeply committed to providing a safe culture that builds respect, fosters inclusiveness, and values diversity. We celebrate individual strengths and team members from all backgrounds are encouraged to bring their whole selves to work. Our global workforce drives and promotes an inclusive culture, both within our organisation and throughout the communities we interact with across the world. Diverse backgrounds include First Nations Peoples, people with differing abilities, LGBTIQ+ community, gender, neurodiverse, cultural diversity, all age groups, and those with an intersectional or multiple diverse characteristics. We encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply.

https://fortescue.com/careers

Internal Candidates / Current Contractors please apply via Success Factors Careers Portal. For further information on how to apply please visit the Fortescue Hub.

Fortescue reserves the right to close applications early should a suitable pool of candidates be identified. Fortescue will never contact you to ask for payment of any kind, whether directly or through a third party.

About the opportunity

We’re looking for a Head of AI Enablement to lead enterprise-wide AI adoption that lifts productivity, trust, and measurable value realisation. Working across Technology, Data, Strategy & Analytics and People & Culture, you’ll embed AI into everyday ways of working and sustain change through responsible use, strong governance, and clear outcomes.

This role is not only about execution, you will own the enterprise AI adoption strategy and roadmap, set the vision, and translate high-level objectives into actionable programs that drive adoption at scale. Embedded within the AI team, you’ll accelerate RACV’s transformation by building capability through champions, training, communications, and value tracking aligned to governance and risk frameworks.

A snapshot of what you’ll be doing

Reporting to the GM AI Core Experience and Enablement, you’ll partner with senior leaders and cross-functional teams to drive adoption of Copilot and other approved generative AI platforms, ensuring AI is used responsibly and delivers enterprise value

Develop and own the enterprise AI adoption strategy and roadmap, and lead execution across the organisation.
Lead the enterprise-wide adoption plan for Copilot and other generative AI platforms, including target cohorts, rollout waves and interventions.
Design and implement change management, learning and communications programs to build AI capability and sustain adoption.
Build and lead an AI Champion Network at scale across all business units, providing playbooks, enablement assets, and ongoing support.
Stay across emerging generative AI platforms (Copilot, GPT, LLMs), interpret model outputs, and collaborate with data scientists and engineers to support scalable, repeatable use cases.
Define adoption KPIs, model ROI, build executive dashboards and report outcomes to the executive committee to track progress and benefits realisation
Embed Responsible AI policies and risk controls into all enablement activity to meet privacy, security, and governance requirements.
Ensure enablement aligns to RACV’s AI management framework, including ethical and transparent use, compliance obligations, data protection and information security processes
Collaborate with GMs and senior stakeholders to align delivery, resolve blockers, and report on adoption outcomes.

What you’ll bring

Excellent stakeholder management and the ability to influence at all levels of the organisation.
Strong analytical and technical capability, including adoption measurement, ROI modelling and executive dashboards.
Proven program and project delivery skills, and confidence operating in a rapidly changing environment.
Strong written, verbal and presentation skills with a talent for making complex concepts simple and actionable.
Excellent AI research skills and critical thinking, with familiarity in Responsible AI policy and governance.

Qualifications & experience

Tertiary qualification in a related discipline; postgraduate study or certification in AI/data science is highly regarded.
Demonstrable AI experience across Copilot, GPT and other LLMs, with the ability to translate technical capability into business value.
Experience developing strategic plans and delivering digital programs at scale.
Experience brokering partnerships with universities, vendors and industry consortia.
Minimum 10 years in an adaptive corporate environment; large-scale transformation experience is desirable

There’s so much on offer when you join RACV with benefits including

Generous discounts on home and car insurance policies and RACV roadside care
Great discounts across all RACV resorts
Discounts from corporate partners that are updated monthly.

Our difference

At RACV, we believe that maintaining a diverse and inclusive workplace is an important element in our continued success. We want our people to feel welcome, supported and appreciated for who they are and what they bring to our business. Who are we?

At Liontown Resources, our Kathleen Valley operation is moving confidently into full-scale production. Following our recent capital raise and significant investment in growth, we're expanding our technical teams to support the long-term success of the mine.

We're now seeking a Control Systems Engineer to join our process plant maintenance and planning team, ensuring our plant control systems are optimised, reliable, and ready to meet the demands of production.

Why join now?

With our production ramp-up in full swing, this is a pivotal time to be part of Liontown. Our focus is on building a safe, reliable, and efficient operation - and this role will directly influence the performance and sustainability of our processing operations.

What you'll be doing

Reporting to the Control Systems and Technology Superintendent, you will:

Provide technical support for the operation, maintenance, and optimisation of plant control systems.

Implement control strategies and system changes on an operating plant safely and efficiently.

Monitor, troubleshoot, and maintain operational technology (OT), PLC, SCADA, and DCS systems.

Conduct system backups, availability and redundancy checks to maintain operational integrity.

Support continuous improvement initiatives, alarm rationalisation, and alarm management.

Partner with the maintenance, operations, and reliability teams to enhance plant stability and performance.

What you will bring

Experience with Citect SCADA, Allen-Bradley PLCs, and HMI programming.

Strong understanding of Operational Technology (OT) systems and virtualization environments.

Experience with Active Directory management and server/PC administration.

Skilled in industrial networking, including Cisco and Allen-Bradley Stratix switches, subnetting, VLAN configuration, and communication protocols such as Modbus TCP and Ethernet/IP.

Familiarity with telemetry systems for remote monitoring and control.

Knowledge of instrumentation, including 4-20 mA loops and scaling principles.

Experience tuning and optimising PID control loops within process control systems.

Exposure to OSIsoft PI systems (PI-AF, PI Vision, SMT) highly desirable.

What we're looking for

We're looking for someone who brings:

Degree qualifications in Electrical, Control Systems, Mechatronics, or related engineering discipline.

Experience as a Control Systems Engineer (or similar) in mining or heavy industry processing.

Knowledge of PLC, SCADA, and DCS systems, with strong problem-solving skills.

Exposure to process plant maintenance planning and reliability strategies.

Strong communication, organisational, and teamwork skills.

Self-motivation and the ability to work independently with initiative.

Ability to meet site requirements, including a current National Police Clearance (or ability to obtain), pre-employment medical, and drug & alcohol screen.

Why Liontown

At Liontown, you'll be joining a company that's helping drive the clean energy future. Our operations are designed with sustainability at their core — powered by renewables and built for long-term impact.

This is your opportunity to take ownership of a pivotal technical role during a major project phase, while enjoying the stability of a long-term site-based position.

Visit: liontown.com to learn more.

AIR6500 will provide a Joint Air Battle Management System capability for the Royal Australian Air Force. The AIR6500 Hardware Engineering Lead as a member in the System Engineering Integration Team (SEIT) has the responsibility for providing technical guidance and ensuring design integrity and consistency of the Hardware components across the program throughout the project lifecycle. Your primary responsibility is to oversee and lead the Hardware technical aspects of the project, ensuring that all design and development activities are completed to the highest standard and meet the required technical specifications.

·         Drive the AIR6500 Hardware solution and interfaces in the architectural model to the AIR6500 solution

·         Review and guidance of Hardware and non-functional related requirements, product trades, and the sell-off approach

About the program:

LMA has entered into an arrangement with BAE, Saab and CoA (MIWS) for the execution of all Combat System Integration work related to the Aegis Surface Combatant fleet. 

The agreement, called the Combat Systems Integration – Integrated Project Team (CSI-IPT) Collaboration Agreement or CCA forms a collaborative enterprise organisation to execute scopes of work across Hobart Class Destroyer (SEA4000 Phase 6 and other related Destroyer Capability Enhancement (DCE) upgrades) and the Hunter Class Frigates (HCFs - SEA5000 Phase 1). The CSI-IPT evolves the current independently executing programs such as SEA4000 Phase  6 and SEA5000 Phase 1 under an umbrella enterprise organisation formed as a program of programs.

• Exposure to custom machinery or safety-critical systems is advantageous
• Australian Citizen or PR

About Toshiba

Established in Australia in 1978, Toshiba International Corporation Pty Ltd (TIC) is a wholly owned subsidiary of Toshiba Corporation, Japan. TIC has established itself as a market leader in the power generation sector in Australia, providing industrial equipment, generators, turbines, transformers, motors, battery energy storage equipment and associated power infrastructure for this industry, including both the supply and installation of new equipment and the maintenance or upgrading of existing equipment. Our Company consists of engineering, technical, commercial and business development staff, with all staff focusing on customer needs (mostly the owners/operators and developers of power stations including thermal, hydro-electric, wind and battery energy storage and transmission and distribution plant).

Job Summary

With the recent growth in Digital Asset Management capability and workload, TIC is seeking a highly motivated Asset Management and Analytics Professional to join the ESS business.  The role is focused on working with our customers during the implementation and operation of our Asset Performance and Condition Monitoring Platform (Digital Twin), based on the EtaPRO® platform (https://etapro.com/).  As such, the role requires a working knowledge of power generation facilities, including steam turbine generator-based systems.  It is anticipated that the ideal candidate will bring process mechanical capability, broad thermodynamic knowledge and experience to this role.

Key Responsibilities:

Apply mechanical / process engineering knowledge across the ESS Asset Performance and Condition Monitoring business operations, including:

Working with the existing team to support the safe implementation and operation of online Digital Twin platforms for Toshiba Power Generation customers in Australia, New Zealand, Southeast Asia and other global regions
